# Cursor Rules — Frontend SIGL

Always read and follow docs/CURSOR_FRONTEND_CONTEXT.md before implementing frontend features.

Use PrimeReact and PrimeIcons as the official UI library.

Use TypeScript.

Use Portuguese Brazilian for UI labels, messages, buttons, validation messages and user-facing texts.

Use English for code names: variables, functions, components, files, folders, hooks and types.

Do not send tenantId manually from the frontend. Tenant context must come from authentication/JWT.

Do not use direct fetch in pages or components. Use the existing API client/services from src/api/client.ts.

Preserve multi-tenancy, authentication, authorization and route protection.

Prefer small, safe and incremental changes.

Reuse existing components, contexts, hooks, routes and API patterns before creating new abstractions.

Use PrimeReact components for buttons, forms, tables, dialogs, toasts, confirmations and feedback.

Always include loading, error, empty state and success feedback when creating screens.

Use the project color tokens from src/styles/prime-theme-tokens.css.

Do not invent loose colors in components.

Do not mix Material UI, Ant Design, Chakra or another UI library unless explicitly requested.

Before finishing, check whether npm run build would pass and fix TypeScript/import errors when possible.
